definition.value: An isoquinolinol that is norsalsolinol substituted by a methyl group at position 2. It is present in normal human brain and also identified in the cerebrospinal fluid of patients with Parkinson's disease.
A member of the class of benzochromenones that is urolithin A in which the phenolic hydrogen at position 8 has been replaced by a beta-D-glucuronosyl group.
A hexanoate ester obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of hexanoic acid (caproic acid) with butan-1-ol. It is a volatile compound found in apples and peaches.
A HEPE that is (5Z,7E,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosapentaenoic acid carrying a hydroxy substituent at position 9.
An O-glycosyl amino acid that is L-lysine in which one of the methylene hydrogens at position 5 has been replaced by an (alpha-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactopyranosyl)oxy group.
A dipeptide obtained by formal condensation of the side-chain carboxy group of L-glutamic acid with the amino group of L-phenylalanine.
